{{Primary sources|date=November 2012}} {{Infobox book <!-- |italic title = (see above) --> | name = International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences | image = International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences.jpg <!-- include the file, px and alt: [[File:Example.jpg|200px|alt=Cover]] --> | caption = | author = [[William A. Darity, Jr.]] | country = | language = | series = | subject = [[Social science]] | publisher = [[Macmillan Reference USA]] | publisher2 = | pub_date = 2008 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = | awards = | isbn = 978-0-02-865965-7 | oclc = 162146038 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = [[Encyclopaedia of the Social Sciences]] (1930–35) | followed_by = | wikisource = }} The '''''International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences''''' was first [[publish]]ed in 1968 and was edited by [[David L. Sills]] and [[Robert K. Merton]]. It contains seventeen volumes and thousands of entries written by scholars around the world. The 2nd edition is composed entirely of new articles.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gale.cengage.com/servlet/ItemDetailServlet?region=9&imprint=000&titleCode=M83&type=4&cf=p&id=194787 |title=Gale Catalog – International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences, Edition 2 |publisher=Gale.cengage.com |date= |accessdate=2012-11-18}}</ref> It was published in 2008 and edited by [[William A. Darity, Jr.]], an American economist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gale.cengage.com/iess/content.htm |title=Gale – International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences – Explore the Content |publisher=Gale.cengage.com |date= |accessdate=2012-11-18}}</ref>
Though the 1968 '''''Encyclopedia''''' was initially intended to "complement, not supplant" MacMillan's earlier, fifteen-volume '''''[[Encyclopaedia of the Social Sciences]]''''', which had been published from 1930 to 1967 and was edited by American economists [[Edwin Robert Anderson Seligman]] and [[Alvin Saunders Johnson]], it effectively replaced the earlier '''''Encyclopaedia''''', in practice.<ref>{{cite journal|jstor=1237578|title=The International Encyclopedia of the Social Sciences: A Review Article|first=James P.|last=Cavin|date=1 January 1969|publisher=|journal=American Journal of Agricultural Economics|volume=51|issue=2|pages=268–278|via=|doi=10.2307/1237578}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Encyclopaedia of Social Sciences, Inc. Records, 1927–1934|website= Hampshire College Archives|url=http://asteria.fivecolleges.edu/findaids/hampshire/mah3.html}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|jstor=1885029|title=The Encyclopaedia of the Social Sciences|first=E. A. J.|last=Johnson|date=1 January 1936|publisher=|journal=The Quarterly Journal of Economics|volume=50|issue=2|pages=355–366|via=|doi=10.2307/1885029}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Demography and Social Science|journal=Population studies|first=J. C.|last=Caldwell|date=1 November 1996|publisher=|volume=50|issue=3|pages=305–333|doi=10.1080/0032472031000149516|pmid=11618372}}</ref>
