This is a list of published books about '''[[mushrooms]]''' and '''[[mycology]]''', including their history in relation to man, their identification, their usage as food and medicine, and their ecology.

==Identification guides==

These are larger works that may be hard to take on a hike but help with in depth identification after [[mushroom hunting]].
* {{cite book | last = Kuo | first = Michael | title = Morels | publisher = University of Michigan Press | location = Ann Arbor | year = 2005 | isbn = 978-0472030361 }}
* {{cite book | last = Pacioni | first = Giovanni | title = Simon and Schuster's Guide to Mushrooms | publisher = Simon and Schuster | location = New York | year = 1981 | isbn = 978-0671428495 }}
* {{cite book | last = Stamets | first = Paul | authorlink = Paul Stamets | title = Psilocybe Mushrooms & Their Allies | publisher = Homestead Book Co. Distributed nationally by And/Or Press | location = Seattle Berkeley, Calif | year = 1978 | isbn = 0-930180-03-8 }}
* {{cite book | last = Stamets | first = Paul | authorlink = Paul Stamets | title = Psilocybin Mushrooms of the World: An Identification Guide | publisher = Ten Speed Press | location = Berkeley, Calif | year = 1996 | isbn = 0-89815-839-7 }}

===Europe===

These are identification guides relevant only to [[Europe]].
* {{cite book | last = Bondartsev| first = A.S. | title = The Polyporaceae of the European USSR and Caucasia | publisher =  Program for Scientific Translations | location = Jerusalem, Israel | year = 1971 | oclc = 204648}}
* {{cite book | last = Breitenbach | first = J | title = Fungi of Switzerland | publisher = Mad River Press | year = 1984 | isbn = 978-0916422479 }}
* {{cite book | last = Kavina | first = Karel | title = Atlas des Champignons de l'Europe | publisher = Praha: Chez les éditeurs | year = 1934 | oclc = 3065296 | language = French}}
* {{cite book | last = Lange | first = Jakob | title = Guide des Champignons | publisher = Delachaux et Niestle | location = Neuchâtel | year = 1983 | isbn = 9782603004692 | language = French}}
* {{cite book | last = Lange | first = Morten | title = Notes on the Macromycetes of Northern Norway (Acta Borealia, A. Scientia No. 23) | publisher = Universitetsforlaget | location = Tromsø, Oslo | year = 1967}}
* {{cite book | last = Skirgiełło | first = Alina | title = Fungi: Basidiomycetes, Boletales (Gryzyby)| oclc = 3073155 |   publisher = The Foreign Scientific Publications Dept. of the National Center for Scientific, Technical and Economic Information | location = Warsaw, Poland | year = 1975}}
* {{cite book | last = Sterry | first = Paul | title = Fungi of Britain and Northern Europe | publisher = Chancellor | location = London | year = 1991 | isbn = 978-1851528103 }}
* {{cite book | last = Thompson | first = Peter | title = Ascomycetes in Colour: Found and Photographed in Mainland Britain | publisher = Xlibris Corporation | location = Great Britain | year = 2013 | isbn = 978-1479747559 }}{{Self-published inline|date=January 2018}}

===North America===

These are identification guides relevant only to [[North America]]. Below are sections detailing specific regions of North America, such as the [[Southeastern United States]] and the [[Pacific Northwest]].
