theregister.co.uk/2007/07/23/metapedia/print.html |archivedate=9 March 2011 |deadurl=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Schweyer |first=Cléo |title=L'extrême droite s'offre une seconde jeunesse sur le web |work=cafebabel.fr |publisher=Babel International |language=French |accessdate=9 March 2011 |date=2009-07-15 |url=http://www.cafebabel.fr/article/30692/extreme-droit-fn-politique-europe-parti.html |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5x3EcjvPe?url=http://www.cafebabel.fr/article/30692/extreme-droit-fn-politique-europe-parti.html |archivedate=9 March 2011 |deadurl=yes |df= }}</ref><ref name="report08">[http://www.mik.nrw.de/uploads/media/Verfassungsschutzbericht_2008.pdf "Metapedia" als nationales Pendant zu "Wikipedia"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130515045948/http://www.mik.nrw.de/uploads/media/Verfassungsschutzbericht_2008.pdf |date=15 May 2013 }} (i.e "Metapedia" as a nationalist counterpart to "Wikipedia") from: "Report by the NRW Office for the Protection of the Constitution for the year 2008" by the [[Ministry of Interior]] of [[North Rhine-Westphalia]]. pp. 59f. {{de icon}}</ref> The site describes itself as focusing on [[culture of Europe|European culture]], [[art of Europe|art]], science, philosophy, and politics. It was officially launched on 26 October 2006 with the Swedish-language edition.<ref name=Metapedintro>{{cite web |title= Metapedia – Introduction |work= metapedia.org |publisher= Metapedia <!-- |accessdate=8 March 2011 |url= http://www.metapedia.org/ |archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/5x2lxmyzy?url=http://www.metapedia.org/ |archivedate= 2011-03-08 -->}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title= Versionshistorik för "Huvudsida" |work= sv.metapedia.org |publisher= Metapedia |language= Swedish <!-- |accessdate=8 March 2011 |url= http://sv.metapedia.org/m/index.php?title=Huvudsida&offset=20090409222352&limit=500&action=history |archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/5x2grGceL?url=http://sv.metapedia.org/m/index.php?title%3DHuvudsida%26offset%3D20090409222352%26limit%3D500%26action%3Dhistory |archivedate= 2011-03-08 -->}}</ref> The English edition was launched on 28 April 2007.<ref name=Metapedintro/><ref>{{cite web |title= Revision history of "Main Page" |work= en.metapedia.org |publisher= Metapedia <!-- |accessdate=8 March 2011 |url= http://en.metapedia.org/m/index.php?title=Main_Page&offset=20070731115303&limit=500&action=history |archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/5x2lEvErm?url=http://en.metapedia.org/m/index.php?title%3DMain_Page%26offset%3D20070731115303%26limit%3D500%26action%3Dhistory |archivedate= 2011-03-08 -->}}</ref> The Hungarian edition has the most articles: 144,189 as of 27 September 2013.<ref>{{cite web |title= Kezdőlap |work= hu.metapedia.org |publisher= Metapedia |language= Hungarian <!-- |accessdate=27 September 2013 |url= http://hu.metapedia.org/wiki/Kezd%C5%91lap -->}}</ref>
==History== The Swedish Metapedia was founded in 2006 by Anders Lagerström (born October 14, 1977), a [[neo-Nazi]] publisher from Linköping, Sweden.<ref>{{cite web|author=Popkonsertbloggen |url=http://www.corren.se/nyheter/linkoping/nazistsida-blir-fall-for-jk-4185002.aspx |title=Nazistsida blir fall för JK - Linköping - Corren.se - Nyheter Linköping Östergötland |language=sv |publisher=Corren.se |date=2007-02-08 |accessdate=2015-09-01}}</ref>
{{Quote|Anders Lagerström has long been involved in extreme right-wing organizations. In 2000, he was convicted of spraying tear gas in the face of a police officer. In 2002 he started the Nordic publishing house, which specializes in issuing and selling Nazi literature and white power music. Lagerström is also a prominent figure in the [[w:sv:Nordiska förbundet|Nordic Federation]]. The Nazi organization seems to be creating a "Nordic nation state". The organization's website says the following about how this imaginary nation should look: "It means a society populated by a people, and a state power and mass media entirely under Nordic control."<ref>{{cite web|author=Popkonsertbloggen |url=http://www.corren.se/nyheter/nazist-anhallen-for-grovt-ran-4146657.aspx |title=Nazist anhållen för grovt rån - Nyheter - Corren.se - Nyheter Linköping Östergötland |language=sv |publisher=Corren.se |date= |accessdate=2015-09-01}}</ref>}}
Metapedia does not mention Lagerström's connections to the Swedish [[far-right]] on any of its sites, instead stating it as an "electronic encyclopedia which focuses on culture, art, science, philosophy and politics."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.metapedia.org/wiki/Main_Page|title=Main Page - Metapedia|website=en.metapedia.org|language=en|access-date=2018-08-21}}</ref>
Swedish historian [[Rasmus Fleischer]] wrote that:
{{Quote|In 2007, another network began to crystallize within Europe's radical right but with a vastly different ideological character. Activists from the Swedish group Nordiska Förbundet made a coordinated effort to use the internet to propagate a more 'positive' image of {{sic|[[Neo-fascism|neo fascist]]}}, [[third position]] and national revolutionary politics. They created a blog portal (Motpol.nu), a web community (Nordisk.nu) and a wiki site (Metapedia). Today there exist a dozen editions of Metapedia, making it a vital medium for dissemination of the ideology labeled here as "multi-fascism". Metapedia tends to promote antisemitism in a cautious way, not stating too much in words but instead using the hyperlinked wiki format to make insinuations about a [[Jewish conspiracy]].<ref>{{cite book|first=Rasmus |last=Fleischer|authorlink1=Rasmus Fleischer |chapter=Two Fascism|editor1-last=Deland|editor1-first=Mats|editor2-last=Minkenberg|editor2-first=Michael|editor3-last=Mays|editor3-first=Cristin|title=In the Tracks of Breivik: Far Right Networks in Northern and Eastern Europe|date=2014|publisher=Lit Verlag|isbn=978-3643905420|page=63}}</ref>}}
==Content== The site's mission statement states one of its goals is "to present a more balanced and fair image of the pro-European struggle for the general public as well as for academics, who until now have been dependent on strongly biased and hostile 'researchers' like ''[[Searchlight (magazine)|Searchlight]]'', [[Anti-Defamation League]], [[Southern Poverty Law Center]], [[Simon Wiesenthal Centre]], and such."<ref>{{cite web |title= Metapedia: Mission statement |work= en.metapedia.org |publisher= Metapedia |date= 2010-06-17 |accessdate=9 March 2011 <!-- |url= http://en.metapedia.org/wiki/Metapedia:Mission_statement |archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/5x33uimgC?url=http://en.metapedia.org/wiki/Metapedia:Mission_statement |archivedate= 2011-03-09 -->}}</ref> The Metapedia logo features the head of a sculpture ("''Youth''") by the German artist [[Arno Breker]],<ref>{{cite web |title= Metapedia: Projektbeschreibung |work= de.metapedia.org |publisher= Metapedia |language=German |date= 2011-01-24 |accessdate=9 March 2011 <!-- |url= http://de.metapedia.org/wiki/Metapedia:Projektbeschreibung |archiveurl= https://www.webcitation.org/5x30gQwoE?url=http://de.metapedia.org/wiki/Metapedia:Projektbeschreibung |archivedate= 2011-03-09 -->}}</ref> whose works were endorsed by the Nazi authorities as the antithesis of degenerate art.<!-- See "Arno Breker" page for citation -->
The site has more than 20,000 articles in English; topics covered include [[European history]], [[Norse mythology]], and white nationalist music.<ref name="splc">{{cite news|title=Aryan Encyclopedia Takes Off |work=Intelligence Report |publisher=[[Southern Poverty Law Center]] |location=[[Montgomery, Alabama]] |accessdate=1 April 2018 |year=2007 |url=https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/intelligence-report/2007/aryan-encyclopedia-takes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/5x388LxL9?url=http://www.splcenter.org/get-informed/intelligence-report/browse-all-issues/2007/winter/white-nationalism |archivedate=9 March 2011 |deadurl=no}}</ref> ''[[The Register]]'' states that "a good percentage of Metapedia's content seems to be dedicated to [[Woden]], the [[White Order of Thule]], [[runes]], and other subject matter which would undoubtedly have found favour with Aryan hocus-pocus aficionado [[Heinrich Himmler]]."<ref name="register"/> ''[[Crítica de la Argentina]]'' says Metapedia has glowing descriptions of [[Adolf Hitler]] and other Nazi figures.<ref>[http://es.scribd.com/doc/159125419/Diario-Critica-2008-06-07 {{lang|es|Llegó la Wikipedia de ultraderecha}}], [[Crítica de la Argentina]] {{es icon}}</ref> [[Daniel Goldhagen]] describes it as seeking "to create (currently in 18 languages) an [[anti-Semitic]] informational universe."<ref>{{cite news|last=Goldhagen|first=Daniel|title=How the Web spreads anti-Semitism|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/10/18/opinion/goldhagen-anti-semitism-internet/?hpt=hp_bn7|accessdate=5 November 2013|newspaper=[[CNN]]|date=18 October 2013|authorlink=Daniel Goldhagen}}</ref>
According to the [[North Rhine-Westphalia]]n [[Office for the Protection of the Constitution]], Metapedia's articles are characterized by [[historical negationism]] and lauding [[Nazi Germany]].<ref name="report08"/> For this reason, the German [[Federal Department for Media Harmful to Young Persons]] ({{lang|de|Bundesprüfstelle für jugendgefährdende Medien}}) started an [[Federal Department for Media Harmful to Young Persons#The indexing process|indexing process]], which would consider as to whether Metapedia is "harmful to young people".<ref name="bulletin1610215">[http://dip21.bundestag.de/dip21/btd/16/102/1610215.pdf Bulletin of the German Parliament 16/10215] from 12 September 2008, pp. 6f.: Answer of the German government to a parliamentary query by the Green Member of the German Parliament Monika Lazar {{de icon}}</ref>
In early 2007, within half a year of the launching of the original Swedish edition, Metapedia received much Swedish media attention for its similarity to Wikipedia and some of its contents, in particular for its positive characterization of many Nazi German personalities, for cataloguing [[Jews]] in [[Swedish media]], and for characterizing Swedish companies as either "Swedish-owned" or "Jewish-owned".<ref>[http://www.dn.se/kultur-noje/debatt-essa/judeforfoljelser-pa-internet {{lang|sv|Judeförföljelser på internet}}] [[Dagens Nyheter]], 8 February 2007 {{sv icon}}</ref><ref>[http://www.kristianstadsbladet.se/kultur/article1042977/Propagandapedia.html Propagandapedia] [[Kristianstadsbladet]], 20 February 2007 {{sv icon}}</ref> This led to an investigation by the [[Chancellor of Justice (Sweden)|Chancellor of Justice]] ({{lang|sv|Justitiekanslern}}) to decide whether the site should be prosecuted for inciting hatred or for violating the Swedish [[Privacy Law]] ({{lang|sv|[[:sv:Personuppgiftslagen|Personuppgiftslagen]]}}).<ref name="corren0729b">[http://www.corren.se/ostergotland/linkoping/?articleId=4185002 {{lang|sv|Nazistsida blir fall för JK}}] [[Östgöta Correspondenten]], 9 February 2007 {{sv icon}}</ref> After reviewing the site's contents, the Chancellor of Justice decided to terminate investigations, since nothing had been found that violated the Freedom of Speech Act ({{lang|sv|[[:sv:Yttrandefrihetsgrundlagen|Yttrandefrihetsgrundlagen]]}}) or the Privacy Law.<ref>[http://www.sr.se/ostergotland/nyheter/artikel.asp?artikel=1213676 {{lang|sv|Ingen förundersökning kring Metapedia}}] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080205070731/http://www.sr.se/ostergotland/nyheter/artikel.asp?artikel=1213676 |date=5 February 2008}}, Sveriges Radio Östergötland, 20 February 2007 {{sv icon}}</ref> In January 2009, in a response to further attention given to the site, the Swedish Chancellor of Justice opined that Metapedia presented a positive image of Adolf Hitler, but decided not to restart an investigation since this was not illegal.<ref>[http://www.fgj.se/Filuppladdning.asp?did=202&OmrID=4&SubID=110&SubSubID=0 {{lang|sv|JK: Positiv text om Hitler inte hets mot folkgrupp}}]{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes}} Föreningen Grävande Journalister, 26 January 2009 {{sv icon}}</ref>
==Operation== Metapedia runs on [[MediaWiki]], a [[free and open-source software|free and open-source]] [[wiki software]] platform written in [[PHP]] and built upon the [[MySQL]] database.<ref name="bulletin1610215"/><ref>[http://www.dn.se/kultur-noje/debatt-essa/judeforfoljelser-pa-internet-1.646996 Judeförföljelser på internet], [[Dagens Nyheter]], 8 February 2007 {{sv icon}}</ref><ref name="corren0729">[http://www.corren.se/archive/2007/2/9/j2hmaalwr3pyawb.xml?category1=1096984640-4&category2=1096984640-7& Extremisternas "uppslagsverk" kan vara olagligt]{{Dead link|date=November 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}, [[Östgöta Correspondenten]], 9 February 2007 {{sv icon}}</ref>
Metapedia is headed by Lagerström and Lennart Berg, who also runs the supporting NFSE Media AB.<ref name="corren0729b"/>
