{{Infobox book series |name = The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature |language = English |genre = [[Chinese literature]] |publisher = [[Cambridge University Press]] |pub_date = 2010 |number_of_books = 2 |author = [[Kang-i Sun Chang]] and [[Stephen Owen (academic)|Stephen Owen]] (eds.) }}
'''''The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature''''' is a 2-volume history book series published by [[Cambridge University Press]] in 2013.<ref>[http://www.cambridge.org/us/academic/subjects/literature/asian-literature/cambridge-history-chinese-literature ''The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature''], [[Cambridge University Press]].</ref> The books were edited by [[Kang-i Sun Chang]] and [[Stephen Owen (academic)|Stephen Owen]]. Volume 1 deals with Chinese literature before the [[Ming dynasty]], and Volume 2 from the Ming dynasty onward.
==Contents== The volumes of the series are as follows: # ''To 1375'' (edited by [[Stephen Owen (academic)|Stephen Owen]]), 2010. {{ISBN|978-0-521-85558-7}}<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/cambridge-history-of-chinese-literature/76F4628F8A769EEF2DF952B530ED0CEE|title=The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature|editor-first1=Kang-i Sun|editor-last1=Chang|editor-first2=Stephen|editor-last2=Owen|date=7 May 2018|publisher=|journal=Cambridge Core|doi=10.1017/CHOL9780521855587}}</ref> # ''From 1375'' (edited by [[Kang-i Sun Chang]]), 2010. {{ISBN|978-0-521-85559-4}}<ref>{{cite journal|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/books/cambridge-history-of-chinese-literature/6FEBDC1995B8D05749A1F453D7577D21|title=The Cambridge History of Chinese Literature|editor-first1=Kang-i Sun|editor-last1=Chang|editor-first2=Stephen|editor-last2=Owen|date=7 May 2018|publisher=|journal=Cambridge Core|doi=10.1017/CHOL9780521855594}}</ref>
